CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 18, 1959, pg. 3, reads: "Edward Simpson Admits Brutal Slaying of Freda Jackson in Wee Hours' Tryst - Body Found Here - The semi-nude body of Freda Maxine Jackson, 19, was found choked to death, lying in the gutter in this wooded section adjacent to the steps leading from Breckinridge [Brackenridge] St. to Robinson Ct. in Terrace Village II.  Spot marked 'X' shows where body was found.  Railings of the Robinson Ct. can be seen in upper part of photo.  The murder scene location is approximately halfway up steps. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Municipal steps from Brackenridge Street to Robinson Court on wooded hillside, site of murder of Freda Jackson, Hill District
